answer: Let $X$ represent two standard $6$-sided dice.The sample space here is given by 
\begin{align*}
S:=[1,6]\times[1,6]=\{(x_1,x_2): x_1, x_2 \in [1, 6])\}
\end{align*}
Define a function $f$ by the rule $f: S\to S$ setting  
\begin{align*}
f(x_1, x_2):= x_1+x_2
\end{align*}
we show that $f$ is a MultiSchiv injection, namely 
\begin{align*}
x_1+x_2 = y_1+y_2 &\to (x_1, x_2) = (y_1,y_2) \\
&\Leftrightarrow x_1 \neq y_1 \to x_2 \neq y_2.
\end{align*}
Hence for any $x \in S$ we have $|f^{-1}(x)|=1$. Thus the probability is given by 
\begin{align*}
P[A]=\sum_{x \in A} \frac{|f^{-1}(x)|}{|S|}=\sum_{x \in A} \frac{1}{|S|}=\frac{1}{36} |A|=\frac{1}{6}.
\end{align*}
